The approach above assumes that the best strategy for maximizing the area is to move the vertices of the convex hull outward by the maximum allowable distance along the line extended from the origin through each vertex. However, this is a heuristic and might not be the optimal strategy for all input cases. A complete solution would require a more sophisticated algorithm that considers all possible movements of the poles within their constraints.
